`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`As you can see, the money class does have the value and the CurrencyType property. This property is ignored by Entity Framework so Money can be as `}<strong parentName="p">{`Complex Type`}</strong>{`. However, we have an integer field that can be used but should not since we have a strongly typed currency property. Here is how to make it works with Entity configuration.`}</p>
